<p style=3D"mso-line-height-rule:exactly; line-height:175%"><br>As someone =
who's been at the frontier of software for a long time (first with Gatsby, =
now with Mastra), I wanted to create something practical that cuts through =
the hype around AI. Given the right tools and knowledge, anyone can and sho=
uld be able to build a simple agent in just 5 minutes. That=E2=80=99s why t=
his book is intentionally short: it=E2=80=99s meant to get you building in =
as quickly as possible.<br><br></p>
<p style=3D"mso-line-height-rule:exactly; line-height:175%">You'll find tha=
t I've broken everything down into digestible pieces =E2=80=93 from choosin=
g the right LLM to structuring workflows and implementing RAG. The code exa=
mples are meant to be something you can actually use to get a simple, compl=
ete project working in just a day or two.<br><br>In the 2nd edition, you'll=
 also find new sections on MCP, image generation, voice, A2A, web browsing =
and computer use, workflow streaming, code generation, agentic RAG, and dep=
loyment.<br><br></p>
<p style=3D"mso-line-height-rule:exactly; line-height:175%">We're all figur=
ing this out together since the field is moving so quickly (it's been just =
over 30 months since ChatGPT launched!). I hope this serves as a useful sta=
rting point. I=E2=80=99ll be posting more updates in the future and am look=
ing forward to seeing what you build with these principles in mind.<br><br>=
</p>
